{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The adultery of Hosea\uc1\u8217*s wife

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}When the {\scaps Lord} began to speak through Hosea, he said to him:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Go marry an unfaithful woman
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
who will bear you children by her adultery,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for like an adulterous wife the land is unfaithful to the {\scaps Lord}.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}So he married Gomer, the daughter of Dibliam, and when she conceived and bore him a son,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}the {\scaps Lord} said:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Call him \uc1\u8216*Jezreel,\uc1\u8217* for in a little while
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will punish the dynasty of Jehu
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for the blood shed at the valley of Jezreel,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will cause the kingdom of Israel to cease.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}On that day, I will break Israel\uc1\u8217*s bows and arrows
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
in the valley of Jezreel.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}When she conceived again and bore a daughter, the {\scaps Lord} said to Hosea:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Call her Lo-Ruhamah \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*No-Compassion\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for I will no longer have compassion on Israel,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
certainly not spare them.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}But on Judah I will have compassion,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will deliver them by the {\scaps Lord} their God,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
but I will not deliver them by bow nor by sword,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
nor by battle nor by horses nor by horsemen.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}After she had weaned No-Compassion, and when she conceived and bore a son, he said:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}\uc1\u8220*Call him Lo-Ammi \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Not-My-People\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for you, Israel, are not my people,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and I indeed am not your God.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Yet the number of the Israelites
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
will be as the sand of the sea,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
which cannot be measured or counted,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and where they were told, \uc1\u8220*You are not my people,\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
they will be called, \uc1\u8220*children of the living God.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}The Judeans and the Israelites
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
will join together again,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
will appoint for themselves one leader,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
will return to their own land.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Great will be the day of Jezreel!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 2}So call your brothers, My People,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and your sisters, Compassion.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Accuse, accuse your mother:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for she is not my wife,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and I will not be her husband.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Let her put her acts of infidelity out of her sight,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and her lovers from between her breasts,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}else I will strip her bare,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
expose her as she was on the day of her birth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
make her like the wilderness,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
let her become like a parched land,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and let her die of thirst.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}And on her children I will have no pity,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
since they are children of adultery,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}for their mother has become a prostitute,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
she who conceived them has behaved shamefully.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
She has said,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*I will go after my lovers
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
who gave me my bread and my water,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
my wool, my flax, my oil, and my drink.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}That is why I am going to hedge up her ways with thorns,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and build a wall about her,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
so that she cannot find her paths.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}She will pursue her lovers,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
but will not overtake them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
She will seek them,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
but not find them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
In time she will say,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*I will go back to my first husband,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I was better off then than now.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}She herself did not know
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
that it was I who gave her
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the grain, the sweet wine, and the oil,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
who lavished on her silver and gold \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
that they used in worshipping Baal!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9} So I will take back my grain at the harvest,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and my sweet wine in its season.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will withdraw my wool and my flax,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
given to cover her nakedness;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}and so I will strip her naked before her lovers,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and no one shall deliver her out of my hand.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}I will end all her celebrations,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
her yearly feasts, her new moons, and her sabbaths,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
all her festivals.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}I will lay waste her vines and her fig trees,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
of which she says, \uc1\u8220*These are my wages
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
which my lovers have given me.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will make them a thicket,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and the wild animals will eat them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}In this way I will punish her for the days of the Baals,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
in which she made offerings to them,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and decked herself with earrings and jewels,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and went after her lovers,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
but forgot me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8211* declares the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}So I am going to court her,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
bring her into the wilderness,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and speak tenderly to her.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}I will give her from there her vineyards,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and the valley of Achor as a door of hope.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
There she will respond as in the days of her youth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
as in the days when she came up from the land of Egypt.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}At that time, declares the {\scaps Lord},
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
you will call me your husband,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and will no more call me your master.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}I will remove the name of the Baals from her mouth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
their names never again uttered.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}On that day I will make for them a covenant
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
with the wild animals,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the birds of the sky,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and the creatures that crawl on the earth.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will break the bow and the sword,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
banish battle from the land,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and I will make them lie down in safety.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}I will take you for my wife forever,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will take you for my wife in righteousness,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
in justice, in kindness, and in mercy.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}I will take you for my wife in faithfulness,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and you will know the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}On that day I will answer
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8211* declares the {\scaps Lord},
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will answer the empty skies,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and they will answer the dry earth.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}The earth will answer with grain,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and new wine and oil,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and they will answer Jezreel,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}and I will plant her in the land.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will have compassion to No-Compassion,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will say to Not-My-People, \uc1\u8220*You are my people,\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and they will say, \uc1\u8220*You are my God.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 3}Then the {\scaps Lord} said to me, \uc1\u8220*Go again, show love to this woman, who is loved by another, who commits adultery. Love her as the {\scaps Lord} loves the Israelites, though they turn to other gods, and love the raisin cakes offered to idols.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}So I redeemed her for fifteen pieces of silver and a homer and a lethek of barley.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And I told her, \uc1\u8220*You must live with me for many days and you must not sleep around or marry another. And I will do the same for you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}And like this the Israelites will live for a long time without king and without prince, without sacrifice and without pillar, without ephod and without teraphim.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Yet afterward the Israelites will return, and seek the {\scaps Lord} their God and their Davidic king, and in the days to come they will turn with awe to the {\scaps Lord} and his goodness.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Lord\uc1\u8217*s case against Israel

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 4}Hear the {\scaps Lord}\uc1\u8217*s message, Israelites,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for the {\scaps Lord} has brought charges against the inhabitants of the land,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for there is no fidelity, nor true love,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
nor knowledge of God in the land,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}but cursing, lying, and murder,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
stealing, committing adultery, and deeds of violence,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and acts of bloodshed quickly follow each other.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Therefore the land mourns,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
all its inhabitants languish,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the wild animals and the birds of the skies,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
even the fish of the sea are dying.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Yet let no one bring charges,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
let none accuse,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for your people are like those,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
who bring charges against a priest{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn   Heb. uncertain. }.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}You stumble by day,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and the prophet stumbles with you by night,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and I will destroy your mother.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}My people are being destroyed for lack of knowledge;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
because you have rejected knowledge
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I reject you from being priest to me.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Since you have forgotten the teaching of your God,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I also will forget your children.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}The more priests there are, the more they sin against me.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will change their dignity to dishonor.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}They feed on the sin offerings of my people,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
so they hunger after their guilt.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Thus it comes to be, like people, like priest:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will visit upon each punishment for their ways,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and their deeds I will repay them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}They will eat and not be satisfied,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
they will sleep around but stay childless,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
because they have abandoned the {\scaps Lord}
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
to give themselves to{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}prostitution.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Old and new wine take away the understanding.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}My own people ask counsel of a piece of wood!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
A stick gives them advice!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
For a spirit of prostitution has led them astray,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
they commit adultery against their God.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}On the heights of the mountains they sacrifice,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and on the hills they burn incense
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
under oaks and poplars and terebinths,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for their shade is so pleasant.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
