{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
A shoot which has no stalk, yields no fruit
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
If it should yield, strangers would devour it.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Israel is devoured.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Already it lies discarded among the nations
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
like a worthless pot.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}For by themselves they have gone up to Assyria
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
like a wild donkey which wanders by itself.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Ephraim pays for love
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}but even if they sell themselves among the nations,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will round them up.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Soon the kings and princes will writhe under the burden of tribute!
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}For as many altars as Ephraim has erected,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
they are to him altars for sinning,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}were I to write for him ever so many instructions,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
they would be regarded as from a stranger.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}The people love sacrifice, and so they offer sacrifices,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
meat, and so they eat it,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
although the {\scaps Lord} is not pleased with them,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
so now he will remember their guilt,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and punish their sins.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Back to Egypt with them!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}For Israel forgot his Maker and built palaces,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and Judah multiplied fortified cities.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
But I will send fire upon her cities,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and it will devour her strongholds.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The horrors of the coming exile

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 9}Rejoice not too loudly, Israel,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
like the nations,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for you have commited adultery,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
being untrue to your God.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
You have loved a prostitute\uc1\u8217*s wages
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
on every threshing floor.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Threshing floor and wine vat won\uc1\u8217*t feed them,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the new wine will fail them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}They will not stay in the {\scaps Lord}\uc1\u8217*s land,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
but Ephraim will return to Egypt,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and in Assyria they will eat what is unclean.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}They will not pour out libations of wine to the {\scaps Lord},
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
nor please him with their sacrifices.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Their bread will be like the bread of mourners:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
all who eat it will defile themselves.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
For their bread will be only for their hunger,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
it will not come into the {\scaps Lord}\uc1\u8217*s temple.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}What will you do on the day of the festival?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Or on the day of the {\scaps Lord}\uc1\u8217*s feast?
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Even if they flee from destruction,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Egypt will gather them,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Memphis will bury them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Nettles will take possession of their treasure of silver,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
thorns will push into their tents.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}The days of punishment are come,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the days of recompense are at hand,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
as soon the Israelites will know!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*The prophet is a fool,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the inspired man is raving mad!\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
It is because of the greatness of your iniquity
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and the greatness of your hatred.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Ephraim acts the spy with my God,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
a prophet finds the snares of a fowler are in all his ways.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
In the house of his God they lay hostile plots,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}they commit crimes as in the days of Gibeah,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
God will remember their iniquity.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
He will punish their sin.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Israel\uc1\u8217*s corruption

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}I found Israel
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
like finding grapes in the wilderness.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I saw your ancestors
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
like they were the first fruit on a fig tree,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
but as soon as they came to Baal-peor,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
they consecrated themselves to shamefulness,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and became as abominable as the object of their love.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Ephraim \uc1\u8211* like a bird his glory flies away.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
There will be no more birth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
no more motherhood,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
no more conception.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Even though they bring up their children,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will bereave them until not one is left.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Woe to them when I turn away from them!
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Ephraim \uc1\u8211* planted like Tyre in a meadow{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn   Heb. uncertain. LXX: as I have seen, his sons are destined to be a prey },
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
But Ephraim too must lead forth their children to slaughter.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Give them, {\scaps Lord} \uc1\u8211* what will you give?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Give them a miscarrying womb and shrivelled up breasts!
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}All their evil began in Gilgal,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
there I learned to hate them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Because of the evil of their deeds
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will drive them out of my house.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will no longer love them,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for all their princes are rebels.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Ephraim is blighted,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
their root withered.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
If they do bear children,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will slay the darlings of their womb,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}My God will reject them
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
because they have not listened to him,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and they will become wanderers among the nations.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 10}A luxuriant vine is Israel.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
He bore fruit lavishly.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
In proportion to the increase of his fruit
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
he increased altars to idols.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
In proportion to the beauty of his land
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
he made beautiful the sacred pillars.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Their heart is false,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
now they must be punished.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
God himself will break the necks of their altars,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
he will destroy their sacred pillars.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Yes, soon they will be saying,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*We have no king,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for we have not revered the {\scaps Lord},
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and a king, what could he do for us anyway?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Speaking words, perjuring themselves, making agreements,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and litigation springs up like a poisonous weed in a plowed field.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}The inhabitants of Samaria will tremble with fear
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for their calf of Beth-aven.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Its people will mourn over it,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and so will its priests,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
who had rejoiced for its glory,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
now departed from it.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}It will be carried off to Assyria
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
as a present to the patron king.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Disgrace will Ephraim bear
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and Israel will be ashamed of its idol.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}As for Samaria, her king will disappear,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
like foam on the face of the waters.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}And the high places of Aven will be destroyed,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the shrines of Israel\uc1\u8217*s sin,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
thorns and thistles will grow on their altars,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and they will say to the mountains, \uc1\u8220*Cover us,\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and to the hills, \uc1\u8220*Fall upon us.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 What a nation sows, it will reap

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}From the time of Gibeah, Israel has sinned.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
There they took their stand.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Will not war overtake them in Gibeah
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
because of the wicked?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}When I please, I will punish them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Nations will gather against them
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
to chain them for their double crimes.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Ephraim indeed was a trained heifer that loved to thresh grain,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and I myself laid a yoke upon his fair neck{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn   Heb. uncertain. },
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I made Ephraim draw and Judah must plow,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Jacob must turn the soil for himself.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Sow for yourselves righteousness,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
reap the fruits of love.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Break up your fallow ground,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for it is time to seek the {\scaps Lord},
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
so righteousness may come to you{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn   Heb. uncertain }.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}But you have plowed wickedness,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
iniquity have you reaped.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
You have eaten the fruit of lies.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Because you have trusted in your own path{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn   LXX: chariots },
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
in the multitude of your warriors,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}the alarm of war will sound in your cities
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and all your fortresses will be ruined,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
as Shalman laid in ruins Beth-arbel in the day of battle,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
when mothers were dashed to pieces over their children.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Thus will I do to you, Bethel,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
because of the enormity of your wickedness.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
When dawn breaks, so will the king of Israel be broken.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Lord\uc1\u8217*s love for his faithless people

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\cf1\f1\fs22 11}When Israel was young, then I began to love him,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and out of Egypt I called my son.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}The more I called them,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
the further they went away from me.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
They kept sacrificing to Baals
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and making offerings to idols.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Yet it was I who taught Ephraim to walk,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
taking them up in my arms,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
but they did not know that I healed them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}With humane cords I ever drew them,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
with bands of love.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I was to them as one who lifts up the yoke from off their jaws,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and bending toward them, I gave them food to eat.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}No! They return to the land of Egypt,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Assyria will be their king,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
for they have refused to return to me.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Therefore the swords will whirl in their cities,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
will devour in their fortresses{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn   Heb. uncertain }.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}For my people are bent in rebellion against me,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
even if they call on the Most High he will not raise them{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn   Heb. uncertain. }.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}How can I give you up, Ephraim!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Give you over, Israel!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
How am I to give you up as Admah!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Make you like Zeboim!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
My heart asserts itself,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
my sympathies are all aglow.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}I will not carry into effect the fierceness of my anger,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will not turn to destroy Ephraim,
\par}

